{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Sweet Jesus!{\r}

329
00:25:50,381 --> 00:25:51,473
- 不！ - 不！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- No! - No!{\r}

330
00:25:53,951 --> 00:25:55,282
这有很多人过生日
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There were so many birthdays.{\r}

331
00:25:55,386 --> 00:25:58,913
他真是个快乐的好人 他真是个快乐的好人…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}For he's a jolly good fellow For he's a jolly good fellow...{\r}

332
00:25:59,023 --> 00:26:01,617
我们一般不出门 我们会省着用蜡烛
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}So we wouldn't run out, we would spare the candles.{\r}

333
00:26:01,725 --> 00:26:05,752
奎尼 你知道我不喜欢生日 也不喜欢蛋糕
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Queenie, you know I don't like birthdays and I don't like cake.{\r}

334
00:26:06,463 --> 00:26:10,399
死亡也是这里的常客 人们来到这里 又安静离去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And death was a common visitor. People came and went.{\r}

335
00:26:12,236 --> 00:26:14,636
你可以感觉到有人离开了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You always knew when someone left us.{\r}

336
00:26:14,738 --> 00:26:17,229
那时房子里总是寂静无声
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There was a silence in the house.{\r}

337
00:26:31,322 --> 00:26:33,586
这是个值得成长的美好地方
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It was a wonderful place to grow up.{\r}

338
00:26:33,691 --> 00:26:38,151
在这个地方 人们抛开了过往生活中的矛盾
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I was with people who had shed all the inconsequences of earlier life.{\r}

339
00:26:38,862 --> 00:26:42,958
每天只关心天气 洗澡水温度
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Left wondering about the weather, the temperature of a bath,{\r}

340
00:26:44,201 --> 00:26:46,396
一天行将结束时的阳光
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}the light at the end of a day.{\r}

341
00:26:50,808 --> 00:26:54,767
总会有人来重新填补死者的房间
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}For everyone that died, someone would come to take their place.{\r}

342
00:26:55,846 --> 00:26:58,110
我结过5次婚
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I've been married five times.{\r}

343
00:26:58,649 --> 00:27:02,346
我和我的第五任妻子 被临近的食人部落抓住了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}My fifth wife and I are captured by a neighbor tribe of cannibals.{\r}

344
00:27:02,453 --> 00:27:03,511
哦 天哪
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, goodness gracious.{\r}

345
00:27:03,621 --> 00:27:05,088
我们从河里逃跑
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We escaped across the river.{\r}

346
00:27:05,189 --> 00:27:08,556
我的妻子不会游泳 所以很不幸被吃了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}My wife, she can't swim, so, sadly, she eaten.{\r}

347
00:27:08,659 --> 00:27:09,853
哦 天啊
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, my God.{\r}

348
00:27:09,960 --> 00:27:12,793
我的第二任妻子踩到了眼镜蛇 就这么死了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}My second wife steps on cobra and dies.{\r}

349
00:27:13,364 --> 00:27:16,128
嫁给我真是很不幸
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It was very bad luck to be married to me.{\r}

350
00:27:16,233 --> 00:27:19,259
那是欧缇先生 他是我一个熟人的熟人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}That's Mr. Oti. He's an acquaintance of an acquaintance of mine.{\r}

351
00:27:19,370 --> 00:27:21,463
- 第二年夏天我被… - 他是个矮人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- The next summer I'm captured... - He's a Pygmy.{\r}

352
00:27:21,572 --> 00:27:23,437
…巴希勒部落的人抓了 还有其他三个人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}...with three others by the Baschiele tribe.{\r}

353
00:27:23,540 --> 00:27:28,409
他们用我们跟一个奇怪的美国人 换了猪 鞋子和啤酒
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They trade us for pigs, shoes, and beer to a very strange American man.{\r}

354
00:27:47,531 --> 00:27:50,022
听说你并不像看起来那么老
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I hear you're not so old as you're looking.{\r}

355
00:27:50,134 --> 00:27:52,364
大家都被你耍了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You just fooling everybody.{\r}

356
00:27:52,936 --> 00:27:55,962
怎么了？你有马甲本吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What's the matter? Did you get Madjembe?{\r}

357
00:27:56,073 --> 00:27:57,438
什么是马甲本？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What's Madjembe?{\r}

358
00:27:57,541 --> 00:27:58,838
虫子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Worms.{\r}

359
00:27:59,243 --> 00:28:01,507
我身上没虫子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I don't think I have worms.{\r}

360
00:28:02,179 --> 00:28:03,703
我就是这样的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}This is just how I am.{\r}

361
00:28:03,814 --> 00:28:06,681
- 今天吃药了吗？ - 没有 夫人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Did you take your pills today? - No, ma'am.{\r}

362
00:28:06,784 --> 00:28:09,116
来 喝点冰汽水
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Come. Let's get a cold root beer.{\r}

363
00:28:09,219 --> 00:28:11,346
我在枕头下找到了药片
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I found the medication under your pillow.{\r}

364
00:28:11,455 --> 00:28:14,618
我不该去 太危险了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm not supposed to. It's dangerous.{\r}

365
00:28:14,725 --> 00:28:17,455
谁说的？来 小家伙
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Who said that? Come on, little man.{\r}

366
00:28:18,762 --> 00:28:20,423
孩子们好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Hello, children.{\r}

367
00:28:31,675 --> 00:28:33,165
等等
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Hold, please.{\r}

368
00:28:35,846 --> 00:28:40,146
我和费城动物园的猴子关在一起
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Then I'm in the monkey house at Philadelphia Zoological Park.{\r}

369
00:28:41,051 --> 00:28:44,543
第一天就有3000人来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Three thousand people show up my first day.{\r}

370
00:28:45,889 --> 00:28:46,878
看
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Look.{\r}

371
00:28:48,692 --> 00:28:50,592
住笼子里是什么感觉？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What's it like living in a cage?{\r}

372
00:28:50,694 --> 00:28:52,161
臭死了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It stinks.{\r}

373
00:28:52,796 --> 00:28:55,060
可是有猴子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But the monkeys.{\r}

374
00:28:55,866 --> 00:28:57,891
他们会表演戏法
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They do some tricks there.{\r}

375
00:28:58,135 --> 00:29:00,831
我扔矛 和科瓦利打架
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I throw a spear, wrestle with Kowali.{\r}

376
00:29:01,672 --> 00:29:03,401
她是只母猩猩
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She is orangutan.{\r}

377
00:29:03,841 --> 00:29:07,368
不和猴子玩的时候 他们就把我赶回笼子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}When I'm not playing with the monkeys, they want me to run to the bars{\r}

378
00:29:07,478 --> 00:29:09,571
让我咬来咬去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}in my cage, with my teeth.{\r}

379
00:29:19,523 --> 00:29:21,582
之后呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}So then what'd you do?{\r}

380
00:29:21,692 --> 00:29:27,528
后来我离开了动物园 这儿走走 那儿走走 四处游荡
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Then I leave zoo, go here, go there. Wandered most of the time.{\r}

381
00:29:27,998 --> 00:29:29,022
独自一个人？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You were all alone?{\r}

382
00:29:29,133 --> 00:29:31,431
大多数时候都是一个人的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Plenty of time you'll be alone.{\r}

383
00:29:31,535 --> 00:29:34,971
像我们这样的异类 就是这样
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}When you're different like us, it's gonna be that way.{\r}

384
00:29:38,008 --> 00:29:39,839
告诉你个小秘密
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But I'll tell you a little secret.{\r}

385
00:29:39,943 --> 00:29:43,242
无论什么肤色 什么体型
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Fat people, skinny people, tall people,{\r}

386
00:29:43,347 --> 00:29:46,339
人都是孤独的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}white people, they're just as alone as we are.{\r}

387
00:29:46,884 --> 00:29:49,079
但可怕的不是孤独 而是惧怕孤独
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But they're scared shitless.{\r}

388
00:29:55,292 --> 00:29:57,920
我想起了伴我长大的那条河
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I think about the river I grew up on.{\r}

389
00:29:58,395 --> 00:30:01,296
再次坐在河边感觉一定很妙
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It would be nice to sit by my river again.{\r}

390
00:30:03,567 --> 00:30:05,933
走吧 我约了人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Come, I have an appointment.{\r}

391
00:30:08,338 --> 00:30:10,898
我的小家伙来了 准备好了吗 宝贝？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There's my little man. You ready, sugar?{\r}

392
00:30:11,008 --> 00:30:13,340
时刻准备着 时刻准备着
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Always ready. Always ready.{\r}

393
00:30:15,145 --> 00:30:17,238
菲拉门娜 本杰明先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Filamena, Mr. Benjamin.{\r}

394
00:30:18,282 --> 00:30:21,342
- 很高兴见到你 先生 - 我的荣幸 夫人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- It's a pleasure to meet you, sir. - My pleasure, ma'am.{\r}

395
00:30:21,451 --> 00:30:23,419
你认得路回家 对吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You can find your own way home, can't you?{\r}

396
00:30:23,520 --> 00:30:26,250
乘圣查尔斯线到拿破仑路
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Take the St. Charles line to Napoleon.{\r}

397
00:30:32,262 --> 00:30:33,854
嘿！嘿！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Hey! Hey!{\r}

398
00:30:54,184 --> 00:30:57,676
你到底去哪了？进来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Where in God's name have you been? Get in here.{\r}

399
00:30:59,189 --> 00:31:02,454
我急死了 知道吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I mean, you take my breath away, you know that?{\r}

400
00:31:02,860 --> 00:31:05,454
哦 天啊 我担心死了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, Lord, I was so worried about you.{\r}

401
00:31:09,166 --> 00:31:11,726
这是我过得最开心的一天
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It had been the best day of my life.{\r}

402
00:31:12,669 --> 00:31:15,365
- 她的呼吸情况如何？ - 很微弱
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- How's her breathing? - It's shallow.{\r}

403
00:31:15,472 --> 00:31:16,996
他们几小时后会到
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They say it'll reach us in a few hours,{\r}

404
00:31:17,107 --> 00:31:20,008
所以我得把我孩子带到姐姐那去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}so I gotta get my baby and take him to my sister's.{\r}

405
00:31:20,110 --> 00:31:22,578
他们说医院里没什么好担心的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They say there's nothing to worry about here in the hospital.{\r}

406
00:31:22,679 --> 00:31:25,170
若需要 护士会马上过来 你还好吧？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Nurses'll be right here if you need them. Are you okay?{\r}

407
00:31:25,282 --> 00:31:29,013
- 没事 我可以读书 - 一小时内我就会回来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Yeah, I'm okay reading. - I shouldn't be more than an hour.{\r}

408
00:31:30,420 --> 00:31:33,048
有人来陪了吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Was there just company?{\r}

409
00:31:33,624 --> 00:31:36,024
是桃乐茜要走了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It was just Dorothy leaving.{\r}

410
00:31:38,195 --> 00:31:39,628
继续 卡罗琳
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Go on, Caroline.{\r}

411
00:31:39,730 --> 00:31:42,824
“星期天 所有的家人都会来”
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"On Sundays, the families would come and visit."{\r}

412
00:31:43,233 --> 00:31:46,168
那是1930年的感恩节
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It was Thanksgiving, 1930.{\r}

413
00:31:46,270 --> 00:31:49,239
我遇见了那个改变我一生的人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I met the person who changed my life forever.{\r}

414
00:32:01,318 --> 00:32:03,377
本杰明
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, Benjamin.{\r}

415
00:32:03,820 --> 00:32:07,119
你看上去真是出奇地年轻啊
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Might I say you are looking strikingly youthful.{\r}

416
00:32:07,591 --> 00:32:09,149
你好 富勒太太
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Good day, Mrs. Fuller.{\r}

417
00:32:09,259 --> 00:32:12,524
一根拐杖 背也直了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}A single cane, back straight as an arrow.{\r}

418
00:32:12,629 --> 00:32:14,995
你吃了什么灵丹妙药？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What elixir have you been drinking?{\r}

419
00:32:15,098 --> 00:32:18,465
- 谢谢 夫人 - 奶奶！看看我！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Thank you, ma'am. - Grandma! Look at me!{\r}

420
00:32:20,904 --> 00:32:23,236
真不错
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}That was really something.{\r}

421
00:32:23,340 --> 00:32:25,205
快过来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Come on over here, you.{\r}

422
00:32:25,342 --> 00:32:28,140
这是我孙女 黛西
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Now, this is my granddaughter, Daisy.{\r}

423
00:32:29,079 --> 00:32:30,910
这位是…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}This is Mr...{\r}

424
00:32:31,048 --> 00:32:34,711
不好意思 本杰明 我还不知道你姓什么
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm afraid, Benjamin, I don't rightly know your last name.{\r}

425
00:32:34,818 --> 00:32:36,445
叫我本杰明就行了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Benjamin's fine.{\r}

426
00:32:37,087 --> 00:32:39,419
我永远忘不了她那双蓝眼睛
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I never forgot her blue eyes.{\r}

427
00:32:39,856 --> 00:32:42,518
各位 晚餐准备好了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Good people, supper is served.{\r}

428
00:32:42,626 --> 00:32:48,724
为了健康和食物 为了爱和友谊 为了上帝赐予的一切
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Health and food, for love and friends. For everything thy goodness sends.{\r}

429
00:32:49,166 --> 00:32:50,326
阿门
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Amen.{\r}

430
00:32:50,434 --> 00:32:51,662
- 阿门！ - 阿门！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Amen! - Amen!{\r}

431
00:32:55,372 --> 00:32:57,932
你们知道火鸡并不是鸟吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Did you know turkeys aren't really birds?{\r}

432
00:32:58,041 --> 00:32:59,065
怎么说？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Why do you say that?{\r}

433
00:32:59,176 --> 00:33:02,304
他们属于雉科 基本不会飞
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They're in the pheasant family, can't hardly fly.{\r}

434
00:33:02,412 --> 00:33:04,937
不觉得这很可怜吗？不会飞的鸟？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It's sad, don't you think? Birds that can't fly?{\r}

435
00:33:05,048 --> 00:33:07,209
我喜欢不会飞的鸟
