769
00:57:44,426 --> 00:57:46,394
都会给我寄明信片
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Every place he worked.{\r}

770
00:57:47,729 --> 00:57:50,789
纽芬兰 巴芬湾
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Newfoundland. Baffin Bay.{\r}

771
00:57:51,400 --> 00:57:54,460
格拉斯哥 利物浦 纳尔维克
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Glasgow. Liverpool. Narvik.{\r}

772
00:57:55,270 --> 00:58:00,003
他和迈克船长一起去的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He had gone with that Captain Mike.{\r}

773
00:58:02,044 --> 00:58:04,274
迈克船长和莫兰兄弟拖船打捞公司
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Captain Mike had contracted for three years{\r}

774
00:58:04,379 --> 00:58:06,677
签了3年的合约
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}with Moran Brothers Tug and Salvage.{\r}

775
00:58:06,782 --> 00:58:10,650
旧船装上了柴油机和新的绞车
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}The old ship had been refitted with a diesel engine and a new sea winch.{\r}

776
00:58:10,752 --> 00:58:13,653
我们绕过了佛罗里达 沿着大西洋海岸北上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We went around Florida and up the Atlantic seaboard.{\r}

777
00:58:13,755 --> 00:58:17,156
船上现在有7名船员了 迈尔船长和我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We were a crew of seven now. Captain Mike and me.{\r}

778
00:58:17,259 --> 00:58:20,592
厨师 来自特拉华州威灵顿的普兰提斯・梅斯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Cookie, Prentiss Mayes from Wilmington, Delaware.{\r}

779
00:58:20,696 --> 00:58:23,096
布罗迪双胞胎 里克和维克
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}The Brody twins, Rick and Vic,{\r}

780
00:58:23,198 --> 00:58:25,428
在海上这兄弟俩相处很好 但不知什么原因
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}who got along fine at sea but, for some reason,{\r}

781
00:58:25,534 --> 00:58:28,594
一旦回到陆地 他们就不对盘
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}once they were on dry land couldn't stand the sight of each other.{\r}

782
00:58:28,704 --> 00:58:32,265
你知道的 每八艘船就有一艘永远回不来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You know, one in every eight boats never returns.{\r}

783
00:58:32,374 --> 00:58:34,501
一个叫约翰・格林的 人如其名
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There was John Grimm, who sure fit his name.{\r}

784
00:58:34,610 --> 00:58:36,441
全体船员在海上失踪了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}All hands lost at sea.{\r}

785
00:58:36,545 --> 00:58:38,775
来自南达科他州的贝尔维迪市
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}From Belvedere, South Dakota.{\r}

786
00:58:40,182 --> 00:58:43,015
还有来自北卡罗来纳州阿什维尔的 普莱森特・柯蒂斯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And Pleasant Curtis from Asheville, Notch.{\r}

787
00:58:43,118 --> 00:58:46,281
从不跟人说话 除了他自己
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Never said a word to anyone, except himself.{\r}

788
00:58:48,690 --> 00:58:51,284
我经常给他写信
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I wrote him constantly.{\r}

789
00:58:52,928 --> 00:58:57,922
我告诉他我受邀参加纽约市
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I told him I had been invited to audition in New York City{\r}

790
00:58:58,500 --> 00:59:01,162
一所美国芭蕾学校的面试
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}for the School of American Ballet.{\r}

791
00:59:01,270 --> 00:59:02,669
请留下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Please stay.{\r}

792
00:59:02,771 --> 00:59:04,898
谢谢 谢谢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Thank you. Thank you.{\r}

793
00:59:06,875 --> 00:59:08,137
你可以留下来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You can stay.{\r}

794
00:59:10,646 --> 00:59:13,706
可我在团里并不出名
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But I was relegated to the corps.{\r}

795
00:59:14,049 --> 00:59:16,415
只不过是个跳舞的流浪者
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Another dancing gypsy.{\r}

796
00:59:20,722 --> 00:59:22,246
本杰明！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Benjamin!{\r}

797
00:59:22,891 --> 00:59:25,359
第一次见你时
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}How is it when you showed up{\r}

798
00:59:25,460 --> 00:59:29,328
你比那个系船柱大不了多少 还一只脚踩进了棺材
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}you were no bigger than a bollard with one foot in the grave,{\r}

799
00:59:29,431 --> 00:59:33,629
而现在 是我喝多了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}but now, either I drink a hell of a lot more than I think I do,{\r}

800
00:59:34,903 --> 00:59:36,530
还是你长个了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}or you sprouted?{\r}

801
00:59:37,439 --> 00:59:39,202
你有什么秘密？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What's your secret?{\r}

802
00:59:40,642 --> 00:59:42,200
船长
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, Captain,{\r}

803
00:59:44,012 --> 00:59:45,809
你确实喝多了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}you do drink a lot.{\r}

804
00:59:50,619 --> 00:59:54,885
我们住在一个小旅馆里 名字不错 叫冬宫
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We stayed in a small hotel with a grand name, The Winter Palace.{\r}

805
00:59:54,990 --> 00:59:57,754
你根本不知道自己在说什么
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You have no idea what you're talking about.{\r}

806
00:59:57,859 --> 01:00:01,317
蜂鸟不是一般的鸟类
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}The hummingbird is not just another bird.{\r}

807
01:00:02,064 --> 01:00:05,761
它的心率达到每分钟1200下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Its heart rate's 1,200 beats per minute.{\r}

808
01:00:07,536 --> 01:00:10,232
它的翅膀每秒扇动80次
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Its wings beat 80 times a second.{\r}

809
01:00:12,174 --> 01:00:15,166
要是让它无法扇动翅膀
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}If you was to stop their wings from beating,{\r}

810
01:00:15,811 --> 01:00:18,644
不到10秒就会死掉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}it would be dead in less than 10 seconds.{\r}

811
01:00:19,648 --> 01:00:22,310
这不是一般的鸟
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}This is no ordinary bird.{\r}

812
01:00:22,985 --> 01:00:25,078
简直就是奇迹
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}This is a frickin' miracle.{\r}

813
01:00:28,256 --> 01:00:32,158
人们用影像慢放扇翅膀的动作
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They slowed down their wings with moving pictures,{\r}

814
01:00:32,828 --> 01:00:35,023
知道他们看到了什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}and you know what they saw?{\r}

815
01:00:35,530 --> 01:00:38,328
它们的翼尖像这样运动
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Their wingtips are doing that.{\r}

816
01:00:42,371 --> 01:00:46,205
知道数字8有什么数学含义吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You know what the figure eight is the mathematical symbol for?{\r}

817
01:00:49,211 --> 01:00:50,735
无穷
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Infinity.{\r}

818
01:00:50,846 --> 01:00:52,177
无穷！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Infinity!{\r}

819
01:00:55,684 --> 01:00:58,585
每个人 不论语言和肤色有何差异
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Everybody, no matter what differences they had,{\r}

820
01:00:58,687 --> 01:01:02,714
却都有一个共同点
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}the languages, the color of their skin, had one thing in common.{\r}

821
01:01:03,659 --> 01:01:06,025
每晚都会喝醉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They were drunk every single night.{\r}

822
01:01:06,128 --> 01:01:07,652
三楼 谢谢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Three, please.{\r}

823
01:01:07,763 --> 01:01:09,355
能等一下吗 亲爱的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Could you hold, dear, for us, please?{\r}

824
01:01:09,464 --> 01:01:11,728
非常感谢 晚上好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Thank you very much. Good evening.{\r}

825
01:01:11,833 --> 01:01:14,529
她叫伊丽莎白・艾伯特
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Her name was Elizabeth Abbott.{\r}

826
01:01:14,636 --> 01:01:17,935
她并不漂亮 很平凡
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She was not beautiful. She was plain as paper.{\r}

827
01:01:18,040 --> 01:01:20,838
但在我看来她很美
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But she was pretty as any picture to me.{\r}

828
01:01:22,144 --> 01:01:24,169
你在看什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What are you looking at?{\r}

829
01:01:26,415 --> 01:01:28,940
你该知道 我们有个长期协议
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}If you must know, we have a longstanding agreement{\r}

830
01:01:29,051 --> 01:01:30,416
不醉不归
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}never to go to bed sober.{\r}

831
01:01:30,519 --> 01:01:32,919
- 对吗 亲爱的？ - 随你怎么说 亲爱的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Isn't that right, darling? - Whatever you say, darling.{\r}

832
01:01:33,021 --> 01:01:35,080
她丈夫是沃尔特・艾伯特
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Her husband was Walter Abbott.{\r}

833
01:01:35,190 --> 01:01:39,092
他是英国贸易代表团在摩尔曼斯克的首席部长
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He was Chief Minister of the British Trade Mission in Murmansk,{\r}

834
01:01:39,194 --> 01:01:40,821
而且他还是个间谍
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}and he was a spy.{\r}

835
01:01:40,929 --> 01:01:43,796
- 亲爱的 - 哦 谢谢 亲爱的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Darling. - Oh, thank you, my darling.{\r}

836
01:01:43,899 --> 01:01:45,924
- 钥匙 亲爱的 - 噢 对
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Key, darling. - Oh, yes.{\r}

837
01:01:50,439 --> 01:01:53,465
我的一只鞋跟断了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I broke my heel off one of my shoes.{\r}

838
01:01:53,575 --> 01:01:57,170
我不习惯只穿袜子走路
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm not in the habit of walking about in my stocking feet.{\r}

839
01:02:01,583 --> 01:02:03,744
那里白天很长
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They were long days there.{\r}

840
01:02:11,259 --> 01:02:13,227
夜晚更加漫长
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And even longer nights.{\r}

841
01:02:15,430 --> 01:02:18,991
有一个晚上 我辗转难眠
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}One particular night, I was having trouble sleeping.{\r}

842
01:02:20,435 --> 01:02:21,959
抱歉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm sorry.{\r}

843
01:02:23,839 --> 01:02:25,568
我睡不着
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I couldn't sleep.{\r}

844
01:02:38,487 --> 01:02:41,945
我要去泡些茶 你要吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I was gonna make some tea. Would you like some?{\r}

845
01:02:42,858 --> 01:02:44,689
哦 不用了 谢谢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, no. Thank you.{\r}

846
01:03:22,531 --> 01:03:24,089
牛奶？还是蜂蜜？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Milk? Honey?{\r}

847
01:03:24,733 --> 01:03:26,667
一点蜂蜜 谢谢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}A bit of honey, please.{\r}

848
01:03:27,202 --> 01:03:28,965
我希望你不介意蜂蜜里有苍蝇
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I hope you like flies in your honey.{\r}

849
01:03:29,070 --> 01:03:30,731
哦 还是算了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, perhaps not.{\r}

850
01:03:45,587 --> 01:03:49,819
哦 也许多浸一会会更好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, maybe better to let it steep a little.{\r}

851
01:03:50,826 --> 01:03:52,020
浸？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Steep?{\r}

852
01:03:52,394 --> 01:03:53,452
浸泡
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Soak.{\r}

853
01:03:53,728 --> 01:03:57,391
我不知道 我的意思是 泡茶就该这样
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I don't know, I mean, there's a proper way of making tea.{\r}

854
01:03:57,499 --> 01:04:00,730
我家乡那都喜欢喝热茶
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, where I'm from, people just want it to be hot.{\r}

855
01:04:00,836 --> 01:04:02,929
这样啊
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, quite right.{\r}

856
01:04:11,847 --> 01:04:14,247
- 现在你是海员 - 水手
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Now, you're a seaman. - A sailor.{\r}

857
01:04:14,349 --> 01:04:17,079
希望你不要介意 我忍不住想问
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I hope you won't think me impolite, but I have to ask,{\r}

858
01:04:17,185 --> 01:04:19,312
作为一个水手你是不是有点老？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}aren't you a little old to be working on a boat?{\r}

859
01:04:19,421 --> 01:04:22,822
没有年龄限制 只要你能做
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There's no age limit, as long as you can do the work.{\r}

860
01:04:33,635 --> 01:04:35,933
你睡不好是吗？谢谢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And you have trouble sleeping? Thank you.{\r}

861
01:04:36,037 --> 01:04:39,234
以前不这样 通常我睡得像婴儿一样沉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I didn't think I did. I usually sleep like a baby.{\r}

862
01:04:40,208 --> 01:04:42,642
有些事让我睡不着
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Something's been keeping me up.{\r}

863
01:04:43,879 --> 01:04:45,073
我父亲80岁的时候
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}My father, in his 80s,{\r}

864
01:04:45,180 --> 01:04:48,445
深信自己会在睡眠中死去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}he was so convinced he was gonna die in his sleep,{\r}

865
01:04:49,084 --> 01:04:52,212
他约束自己只睡午觉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}he limited himself to having afternoon naps.{\r}

866
01:04:52,988 --> 01:04:55,752
他坚信自己可以逃脱死亡
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He was so determined he was gonna cheat death.{\r}

867
01:04:56,925 --> 01:04:58,790
- 他做到了吗？ - 做到什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Did he? - Did he what?{\r}

868
01:04:58,927 --> 01:05:00,554
睡觉时死了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Die in his sleep?{\r}

869
01:05:02,264 --> 01:05:04,858
他死在自己最喜欢的椅子上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He died sitting in his favorite chair{\r}

870
01:05:04,966 --> 01:05:07,594
听着自己最喜欢的广播节目
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}listening to his favorite program on the wireless.{\r}

871
01:05:07,702 --> 01:05:10,170
他一定已经知道了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He must have known something.{\r}

872
01:05:15,911 --> 01:05:20,974
我的丈夫是英国贸易部长 我们已经在这呆了14个月了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}My husband's the British Trade Minister, and we've been here for 14 months.{\r}

873
01:05:21,082 --> 01:05:24,415
- 天哪  - 本来我们要去北京的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Good God. - We were supposed to go to Peking{\r}

874
01:05:24,519 --> 01:05:27,977
可是看来永远都无法成行了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}but it never seemed to work out.{\r}

875
01:05:29,457 --> 01:05:31,152
你去过远东吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Have you been in the Far East?{\r}

876
01:05:31,259 --> 01:05:33,454
没有 事实上我哪也没去过
