877
01:05:33,561 --> 01:05:35,995
我是说 港口以外的地方
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I mean, outside of harbors.{\r}

878
01:05:36,097 --> 01:05:37,758
你从哪来？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And where is it that you're from?{\r}

879
01:05:37,866 --> 01:05:40,357
路易斯安那州新奥尔良
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}New Orleans. Louisiana.{\r}

880
01:05:41,870 --> 01:05:44,168
我知道那个地方
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I didn't know there was another.{\r}

881
01:05:46,474 --> 01:05:51,502
她跟我讲了她去过的地方 还有她的所见所闻
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And she told me about all the places she had been, and what she had seen.{\r}

882
01:05:53,114 --> 01:05:56,015
我们一直聊到天亮
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And we talked till just before the dawn.{\r}

883
01:05:57,052 --> 01:05:58,519
我只是一个酒鬼
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm just a lush, myself.{\r}

884
01:05:58,620 --> 01:06:03,557
我们回到各自的房间 过各自的生活
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And we went back to our rooms, to our separate lives.{\r}

885
01:06:08,997 --> 01:06:12,296
可每晚我们都会在大厅见面
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But every night, we'd meet again in that lobby.{\r}

886
01:06:17,639 --> 01:06:21,541
午夜的旅馆是一个神奇的地方
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}A hotel in the middle of the night can be a magical place.{\r}

887
01:06:24,412 --> 01:06:27,313
老鼠在远处跑跑停停
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}A mouse running, and stopping.{\r}

888
01:06:28,750 --> 01:06:30,843
暖气炉发出嘶嘶的响声
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}A radiator hissing.{\r}

889
01:06:31,853 --> 01:06:33,718
窗帘在沙沙作响
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}A curtain blowing.{\r}

890
01:06:37,492 --> 01:06:40,859
这样的场景让你感到安静 甚至是温暖
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There's something peaceful, even comforting{\r}

891
01:06:40,962 --> 01:06:44,193
你知道你所爱的人此刻正在熟睡之中
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}knowing that the people you love are asleep in their beds{\r}

892
01:06:44,299 --> 01:06:46,529
而没有什么可以伤害到他们
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}where nothing can harm them.{\r}

893
01:06:49,637 --> 01:06:52,572
伊丽莎白和我都忘记了时间
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Elizabeth and I would lose track of the night{\r}

894
01:06:53,108 --> 01:06:55,269
直到黎明的到来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}until just before daybreak.{\r}

895
01:06:57,879 --> 01:07:00,677
我想我可能让你误解了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I think I may have given you the wrong impression.{\r}

896
01:07:00,782 --> 01:07:02,306
什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Beg pardon?{\r}

897
01:07:02,417 --> 01:07:06,217
已婚女人通常不会在半夜
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, married women don't customarily sit around{\r}

898
01:07:06,321 --> 01:07:08,346
和陌生男人呆在旅馆里
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}in the middle of the night with strange men in hotels.{\r}

899
01:07:08,456 --> 01:07:11,983
我不知道已婚女人什么该做 什么不该做
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I wouldn't know what a married woman does or doesn't do.{\r}

900
01:07:17,766 --> 01:07:19,199
晚安
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Good night.{\r}

901
01:07:21,536 --> 01:07:22,833
摩尔曼斯克
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Murmansk.{\r}

902
01:07:25,473 --> 01:07:28,533
“我遇见了一个人 我坠入了爱河”
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"I've met somebody, and I've fallen in love."{\r}

903
01:07:28,643 --> 01:07:29,837
妈妈？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Mom?{\r}

904
01:07:33,681 --> 01:07:36,206
那是60多年前的事了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}That was over 60 years ago.{\r}

905
01:07:37,519 --> 01:07:38,543
你爱他吗 妈妈？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Did you love him, Mother?{\r}

906
01:07:38,653 --> 01:07:41,417
小女孩哪懂什么爱情？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What does a girl know about love?{\r}

907
01:08:15,023 --> 01:08:16,217
呃…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well...{\r}

908
01:08:18,726 --> 01:08:22,492
- 我穿得不好 - 哦 看起来蛮好 这才像你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- I'm not dressed. - Oh, you look splendid, just as you are.{\r}

909
01:08:24,766 --> 01:08:27,826
在摩尔曼斯克 别浪费时间在酒和奶酪上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Don't waste any time bothering about the wine or the cheese in Murmansk,{\r}

910
01:08:27,936 --> 01:08:30,962
因为这些实在很平常
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}'cause they're really completely ordinary,{\r}

911
01:08:31,072 --> 01:08:36,032
但是鱼子酱和伏特加
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}but the caviar and the vodka{\r}

912
01:08:36,611 --> 01:08:40,707
更显高贵奢华
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}are sublime and plentiful.{\r}

913
01:08:44,519 --> 01:08:45,781
那么
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}So.{\r}

914
01:08:51,092 --> 01:08:52,389
好好尝尝
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Savor it.{\r}

915
01:08:54,529 --> 01:08:56,497
别一下子全吃了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And don't eat it all at once,{\r}

916
01:08:56,598 --> 01:08:59,692
因为那样是享受不到什么的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}because that way, there's nothing left to enjoy.{\r}

917
01:09:01,369 --> 01:09:05,703
现在 口含伏特加 咽下一点点
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And now, take a little swallow of vodka while it's still in your mouth.{\r}

918
01:09:20,588 --> 01:09:23,421
你相处过的女人不多吧？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You haven't been with many women, have you?{\r}

919
01:09:24,626 --> 01:09:26,253
星期天不多
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Not on Sundays.{\r}

920
01:09:28,463 --> 01:09:30,192
你以前从没吃过鱼子酱 对吧？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And you've never had caviar before, have you?{\r}

921
01:09:30,298 --> 01:09:31,925
是的 夫人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}No, ma'am.{\r}

922
01:09:37,772 --> 01:09:39,433
我19岁时
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}When I was 19,{\r}

923
01:09:40,441 --> 01:09:46,710
试图成为第一个游过英吉利海峡的女人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I attempted to become the first woman ever to swim the English Channel.{\r}

924
01:09:47,715 --> 01:09:49,114
真的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Really?{\r}

925
01:09:49,751 --> 01:09:52,777
但那天的水流很急
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But the current that day was so strong that,{\r}

926
01:09:52,887 --> 01:09:55,981
向前游一下 被水流推后两下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}for every stroke I took, I was pushed back two.{\r}

927
01:09:56,591 --> 01:09:59,185
我在水里待了32小时
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I was in the water for 32 hours.{\r}

928
01:10:00,161 --> 01:10:03,995
距离加来两英里时
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And when I was two miles from Calais,{\r}

929
01:10:05,133 --> 01:10:06,862
天开始下雨了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}it started to rain.{\r}

930
01:10:07,602 --> 01:10:09,502
就是这样！保持平稳！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}That's it! Steady on!{\r}

931
01:10:10,038 --> 01:10:12,666
我实在游不动时
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}When I couldn't go any further,{\r}

932
01:10:14,275 --> 01:10:15,708
我停下了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I stopped.{\r}

933
01:10:17,111 --> 01:10:18,703
我只好停下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I just stopped.{\r}

934
01:10:19,314 --> 01:10:24,183
别人都问我 要不要再来一次？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And everybody asked me, would I try again?{\r}

935
01:10:24,919 --> 01:10:26,784
为什么不呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}For why wouldn't I?{\r}

936
01:10:29,691 --> 01:10:31,386
