974
01:14:53,387 --> 01:14:56,481
耻辱的一天…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}a date which will live in infamy...{\r}

975
01:14:56,591 --> 01:15:00,721
这是一场会议 一场事关未来的政治性会议
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It's a meeting, a policy meeting regarding your future,{\r}

976
01:15:01,662 --> 01:15:03,220
可能不止如此
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}possibly beyond.{\r}

977
01:15:04,632 --> 01:15:07,192
伙计们 计划有变
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There's been a change of plan, lads.{\r}

978
01:15:07,401 --> 01:15:09,995
你们或许知道 或许不知道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}As you may or may not know,{\r}

979
01:15:10,104 --> 01:15:12,698
日本人昨天轰炸了珍珠港
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}the Japs bombed Pearl Harbor yesterday.{\r}

980
01:15:13,140 --> 01:15:16,598
富兰克林・德拉诺・罗斯福 要求我们每个人尽到自己的职责
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Frank D. Roosevelt's asked each of us to do our part.{\r}

981
01:15:17,111 --> 01:15:21,207
切尔西号被美国海军征用
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}The Chelsea's been commissioned to serve in the United States Navy.{\r}

982
01:15:21,649 --> 01:15:24,914
负责维修 打捞和营救
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}To repair, to salvage, and to rescue.{\r}

983
01:15:26,454 --> 01:15:30,788
有谁不想打仗 现在说还来得及
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Anybody doesn't want to go to war, now is the time to say so.{\r}

984
01:15:30,892 --> 01:15:35,090
只要你踏上了那艘船 你就是海军了 朋友
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Once you set foot on that boat, you're in the Navy, friend.{\r}

985
01:15:38,332 --> 01:15:41,358
我一直想和你谈谈 迈克
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Yeah, I've been meaning to talk with you, Mike.{\r}

986
01:15:41,469 --> 01:15:43,460
我老婆的情况不好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}My wife's doing poorly.{\r}

987
01:15:43,571 --> 01:15:46,301
我希望能再见她一面
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'd like to maybe see her one more time.{\r}

988
01:15:48,042 --> 01:15:51,842
你现在可以自由地回家了 梅斯先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You're free to make your way home any way you can, Mr. Mayes.{\r}

989
01:15:57,485 --> 01:15:59,248
他走了谁做饭啊？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, if he's leaving, who's gonna cook?{\r}

990
01:15:59,353 --> 01:16:03,414
食物中毒是海上人员死亡的最主要原因之一
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Food poisoning's one of the leading causes of death at sea.{\r}

991
01:16:03,524 --> 01:16:05,890
仅次于安全装备不足
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Right after inadequate safety equipment.{\r}

992
01:16:05,993 --> 01:16:08,621
我会做饭 船长 干了一辈子了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I can cook, Captain. Been doing it all my life.{\r}

993
01:16:08,729 --> 01:16:13,132
我不知道 你也厌战 本杰明
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I don't know. You're a little moody for war, Benjamin.{\r}

994
01:16:13,234 --> 01:16:15,202
管他呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What the hell?{\r}

995
01:16:15,303 --> 01:16:19,637
想打倒小日本和匈奴人的都跟我走
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'll take any man wants to kick the shite out of the Japs and the Huns.{\r}

996
01:16:21,042 --> 01:16:24,808
就这样吧 收拾行装 我们要上战场了 先生们！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}That's it, pack your gear. We're going to war, gentlemen!{\r}

997
01:16:31,686 --> 01:16:33,449
她留了纸条
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She had left a note.{\r}

998
01:16:34,822 --> 01:16:37,552
她写道 “能遇到你真好”
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She wrote, "It was nice to have met you."{\r}

999
01:16:38,326 --> 01:16:39,918
就这样
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And that was it.{\r}

1000
01:16:43,164 --> 01:16:46,224
战争和我们想象的不一样
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It wasn't the war any of us expected.{\r}

1001
01:16:46,334 --> 01:16:49,963
我们只是拖走破损的船 其实都是些废铜烂铁
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We would just tow crippled ships, scraps of metal, really.{\r}

1002
01:16:50,571 --> 01:16:53,540
真有战争 我们也没看到
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}If there was a war, we didn't see it.{\r}

1003
01:16:55,443 --> 01:16:59,504
派给我们的主炮手非常热爱海军
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There was a man assigned to us. The Chief Gunner loved the Navy.{\r}

1004
01:16:59,614 --> 01:17:01,809
最重要的是他爱美国
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But most of all, he loved America.{\r}

1005
01:17:01,916 --> 01:17:04,817
世界上没有其他国家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There is no other country in the world.{\r}

1006
01:17:04,919 --> 01:17:06,011
当你拼写美国…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}When you spell America...{\r}

1007
01:17:06,120 --> 01:17:10,284
他叫丹尼斯・史密斯 是个纯血统的切罗基人 （美洲土著人）
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}His name was Dennis Smith, and he was a full-blooded Cherokee.{\r}

1008
01:17:10,391 --> 01:17:13,485
他的家族在美洲居住了500多年
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}His family had been Americans for over 500 years.{\r}

1009
01:17:13,594 --> 01:17:18,122
去他们的和平主义者 说什么不会凭良心打仗
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}These pacifists. They say they won't fight on conscience.{\r}

1010
01:17:18,232 --> 01:17:21,827
要是所有人都凭良心
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Now, where would be if everybody decided to act{\r}

1011
01:17:21,936 --> 01:17:25,895
- 那会怎么样？ - 冷静点 长官？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- according to their conscience? - Keep it down, would you, Chief?{\r}

1012
01:17:42,123 --> 01:17:45,493
嘿 我观察你很久了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Hey. I've been watching you.{\r}

1013
01:17:46,661 --> 01:17:48,458
你看上去值得信任
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You seem trustworthy.{\r}

1014
01:17:50,264 --> 01:17:52,357
万一我有什么不测
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}If something happens to me,{\r}

1015
01:17:56,437 --> 01:17:58,997
你能答应把这个给我老婆吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}could you see that this gets to my wife?{\r}

1016
01:17:59,106 --> 01:18:03,634
他把全部工钱都给了我 一分钱也没花过
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He'd given me all of his pay. Hadn't spent a dime of it.{\r}

1017
01:18:05,546 --> 01:18:08,811
我希望家人知道 我时刻挂念着他们
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I want my family to know I was thinking about them.{\r}

1018
01:18:13,587 --> 01:18:15,418
全体船员到甲板上！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}All hands on deck!{\r}

1019
01:18:17,925 --> 01:18:20,723
快起来 你们这群懒猪！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Get your asses up here, you lazy bastards!{\r}

1020
01:18:42,016 --> 01:18:44,211
战争终于还是来了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}The war had finally found us.{\r}

1021
01:18:46,921 --> 01:18:48,388
都别动！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}All stop!{\r}

1022
01:18:51,125 --> 01:18:53,116
普莱森特 转下那灯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Pleasant, man that light.{\r}

1023
01:19:01,001 --> 01:19:05,165
一艘载有1300人的运输舰被鱼雷击沉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}A transport carrying 1,300 men had been split by a torpedo.{\r}

1024
01:19:07,575 --> 01:19:09,839
我们是第一个赶到现场的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We were first to arrive at the scene.{\r}

1025
01:19:09,944 --> 01:19:13,505
- 关掉引擎！ - 都别动！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Cut the engines! - All stop!{\r}

1026
01:19:18,652 --> 01:19:20,552
四周只有我们的声音
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We were the only sound.{\r}

1027
01:19:34,502 --> 01:19:35,901
伙计们！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Fellas!{\r}

1028
01:19:45,880 --> 01:19:46,938
潜水艇！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Sub!{\r}

1029
01:19:51,752 --> 01:19:54,550
我们绝对跑不过他们
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We sure as hell can't outrun them fuckers.{\r}

1030
01:19:56,290 --> 01:19:58,588
各就各位！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Battle stations!{\r}

1031
01:20:08,469 --> 01:20:09,458
谢谢 长官
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Thank you, Chief.{\r}

1032
01:20:11,772 --> 01:20:12,864
什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What?{\r}

1033
01:20:25,853 --> 01:20:27,650
是最后一个么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Is that the last one?{\r}

1034
01:21:49,050 --> 01:21:50,350
船长！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Captain!{\r}

1035
01:22:05,950 --> 01:22:08,550
狗日的把我的画打烂了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They shot the hell out of my painting!{\r}

1036
01:22:09,850 --> 01:22:11,650
握着我的手
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Give me your other hand.{\r}

1037
01:22:17,050 --> 01:22:18,050
你会没事的 船长
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You'll be all right, Captain.{\r}

1038
01:22:18,250 --> 01:22:22,450
天使们在天堂里 给你留了个好地方呢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They got a nice spot in Heaven waiting for you. Nice spot.{\r}

1039
01:22:24,050 --> 01:22:27,050
不顺心的时候 你可以像疯狗一样发狂
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You can be as mad as a mad dog at the way things went.{\r}

1040
01:22:30,050 --> 01:22:33,750
可以破口大骂 诅咒命运
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You could swear, curse the Fates.{\r}

1041
01:22:36,050 --> 01:22:38,150
但到头来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But when it comes to the end,{\r}

1042
01:22:40,350 --> 01:22:42,050
还是得放手
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}you have to let go.{\r}

1043
01:22:49,150 --> 01:22:50,350
船长？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Captain?{\r}

1044
01:23:11,150 --> 01:23:14,450
那天 1328人离开了人间
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Thirteen hundred and twenty eight men died that day.{\r}

1045
01:23:16,750 --> 01:23:20,050
我和切罗基人丹尼斯・史密斯道别
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I said my goodbyes to the Cherokee, Dennis Smith.{\r}

1046
01:23:20,950 --> 01:23:24,150
和约翰・格林道别--他猜得没错 他最后还是死在那儿了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}John Grimm, who was right, he was gonna die there.{\r}

1047
01:23:25,750 --> 01:23:28,350
我把普莱森特・柯蒂斯的钱 寄给了他妻子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I sent Pleasant Curtis' wife his money.{\r}

1048
01:23:29,250 --> 01:23:32,350
我向双胞胎的维克・布罗迪道别
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I said goodbye to the twin, Vic Brody,{\r}

1049
01:23:32,450 --> 01:23:37,050
还有迈克・克拉克--切尔西号的船长
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}and to Mike Clark, captain of the tugboat Chelsea.{\r}

1050
01:23:39,550 --> 01:23:44,050
我和那些仍旧怀揣梦想的人道别
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I said goodbye to all the other men who had dreams of their own,{\r}

1051
01:23:44,150 --> 01:23:46,650
他们有的想做保险推销员
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}all the men who wanted to be insurance salesmen{\r}

1052
01:23:46,750 --> 01:23:49,750
有的想当医生 律师 甚至是部落酋长
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}or doctors or lawyers or Indian chiefs.{\r}

1053
01:23:50,750 --> 01:23:52,550
这个修不好了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}This don't get fixed.{\r}

1054
01:23:54,650 --> 01:23:57,750
在那儿 死亡不再是自然发生的了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Out here, death didn't seem natural.{\r}

1055
01:24:14,750 --> 01:24:17,950
我从没在远海上见过蜂鸟
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'd never seen a hummingbird that far out to sea.{\r}

1056
01:24:19,450 --> 01:24:21,050
无论是之前 还是此后
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Before or since.{\r}

1057
01:24:26,850 --> 01:24:33,050
1945年5月 我26岁
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And in May of 1945, when I was 26 years old,{\r}

1058
01:24:33,450 --> 01:24:34,550
我回家了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I came home.{\r}

1059
01:24:35,450 --> 01:24:38,050
我准备好了！准备好了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm ready! I'm ready!{\r}

1060
01:24:38,150 --> 01:24:39,550
来了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm coming!{\r}

1061
01:24:40,450 --> 01:24:44,050
- 我准备好了！ - 这就来了 阿法莉娜
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- I'm ready! - All right, I'm coming, Miss Alfalina.{\r}

1062
01:24:44,150 --> 01:24:45,650
- 奎尼？ - 嗯？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Queenie? - Yes?{\r}

1063
01:24:51,550 --> 01:24:57,450
老天爷！你回来了！ 神啊 你回来了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Sweet Jesus! Oh, you're home! Oh, Lord, you came back!{\r}

1064
01:24:58,350 --> 01:25:00,350
- 快让我瞧瞧 - 他是谁呀 妈妈？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Let me look at you. - Who's that, Mama?{\r}

1065
01:25:00,450 --> 01:25:03,650
- 孩子啊 这是你哥哥 本杰明 - 我都不知道我还有哥哥
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Child, it's your brother, Benjamin. - I didn't know he was my brother.{\r}

1066
01:25:03,750 --> 01:25:05,450
你不知道的事情多了去了 小丫头
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There's a shitload of things you don't know, child.{\r}

1067
01:25:05,550 --> 01:25:06,750
赶紧去把地扫完
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Get on out there and finish sweeping.{\r}

1068
01:25:06,850 --> 01:25:08,950
再把手洗洗来帮我摆餐桌 快去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Come here, wash your hands, help me with the table. Go on, now.{\r}

1069
01:25:09,050 --> 01:25:12,950
转过来 你看起来跟重生了一样！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Turn around. You look like you've been born again.{\r}

1070
01:25:13,050 --> 01:25:15,350
比春天还有活力！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Younger than the springtime.{\r}

1071
01:25:15,450 --> 01:25:19,050
要我说 那牧师施法的时候 肯定是又给了你一条命
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I think that preacher laid hands on you gave you a second life.{\r}

1072
01:25:19,150 --> 01:25:22,850
那会我看着你就知道 你跟别人不一样
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I knew it that moment I saw you, you were special.{\r}

1073
01:25:22,950 --> 01:25:24,750
知道嘛 我的膝盖现在都酸
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I tell you what, my knees are sore,{\r}

1074
01:25:24,950 --> 01:25:27,450
因为我每天晚上都跪着 求上帝保佑
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}'cause I've been on them every night asking the Lord,{\r}

1075
01:25:27,550 --> 01:25:31,250
求他“上帝啊 我只要他平安回家”
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I said, "God, just bring him home safely."{\r}

1076
01:25:31,350 --> 01:25:33,850
还记得我怎么跟你说的吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Remember what I told you?{\r}

1077
01:25:33,950 --> 01:25:35,650
“你永远都猜不到 以后的生活是啥样子”
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"You never know what's coming for you"?{\r}

1078
01:25:35,750 --> 01:25:37,650
没错 快坐下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}That's right. Sit down.{\r}

1079
01:25:39,050 --> 01:25:43,150
这几年 有碰上什么有趣儿的事吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, you learn anything worth repeating?{\r}

1080
01:25:45,250 --> 01:25:49,450
- 当然了 - 你尝过了苦头
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- I sure saw some things. - Oh, you seen some pain.{\r}

1081
01:25:50,950 --> 01:25:53,750
- 也尝过甜头？ - 嗯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Some joy, too? - Sure. Sure, I did.{\r}

1082
01:25:53,850 --> 01:25:57,950
我就是想听你亲口说这些 瞧瞧你呀
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Yeah, that's what I want to hear. Look at you.{\r}

1083
01:25:58,050 --> 01:26:01,550
- 蒂奇上哪儿去了？ - 哦 孩子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Where's Tizzy? - Oh, baby.{\r}

1084
01:26:04,050 --> 01:26:07,950
韦瑟斯走了 上个月 睡觉的时候去的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Mr. Weathers died in his sleep one night last April.{\r}

1085
01:26:08,050 --> 01:26:11,450
- 妈妈 您节哀 - 别操心我了 孩子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Mama, I'm so sorry. - Don't you worry about that, baby.{\r}

1086
01:26:13,250 --> 01:26:15,850
