01:34:22,850 --> 01:34:28,150
也不是说我不想还是怎么的 我只是怕 会让你失望
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It's not that I wouldn't like to or anything. I think I'll just disappoint you.{\r}

1187
01:34:29,050 --> 01:34:32,150
本杰明 我和更老的人都在一起过
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, Benjamin, I've been with older men.{\r}

1188
01:34:32,950 --> 01:34:34,950
明早你就要回纽约了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You're going back to New York in the morning.{\r}

1189
01:34:35,050 --> 01:34:37,350
你该和朋友在一起
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You should be with your friends.{\r}

1190
01:34:38,350 --> 01:34:40,850
- 你只能年轻一次 - 我够大了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- You're only young once. - Oh, I'm old enough.{\r}

1191
01:34:40,950 --> 01:34:43,550
黛西 就是 今晚不行
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Daisy, just not tonight, is all.{\r}

1192
01:34:57,150 --> 01:34:59,250
我们可以去听听音乐
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We could go hear some music.{\r}

1193
01:35:01,550 --> 01:35:04,250
我们的生命 因为各种各样的机遇 而变得更有意义
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Our lives are defined by opportunities.{\r}

1194
01:35:05,050 --> 01:35:07,050
甚至那些我们错过的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Even the ones we miss.{\r}

1195
01:35:07,950 --> 01:35:11,550
你看起来 如此英俊 与众不同
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You look so handsome and so distinguished.{\r}

1196
01:35:11,650 --> 01:35:13,850
据说飓风不会过来 刚好从我们这块刮过去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They're saying the hurricane's gonna miss us, blow right on by.{\r}

1197
01:35:13,950 --> 01:35:18,550
- 太好了 - 我在毯子下面和妈妈一起躺着
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Oh, that's great. - I'll stay under the blankets with Mother.{\r}

1198
01:35:18,650 --> 01:35:22,750
她什么也没说…本杰明你在吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She says nothing... Benjamin?{\r}

1199
01:35:24,650 --> 01:35:25,750
“我的生命…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"Things were becoming different..."{\r}

1200
01:35:25,850 --> 01:35:26,950
又有了不一样的变化
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}... for me.{\r}

1201
01:35:27,150 --> 01:35:30,650
我的头发 越来越黑 像野草一样生长
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}My hair had very little gray and grew like weeds.{\r}

1202
01:35:30,850 --> 01:35:34,550
我的嗅觉更加灵敏 听觉 也加更敏锐
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}My sense of smell was keener. My hearing, more acute.{\r}

1203
01:35:34,650 --> 01:35:37,350
我走得更快更远
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I could walk further and faster.{\r}

1204
01:35:37,450 --> 01:35:43,150
别人都在变老 而我 却独自一人 越来越年轻
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}While everybody else was aging, I was getting younger, all alone.{\r}

1205
01:35:46,250 --> 01:35:47,450
进来吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Come in.{\r}

1206
01:35:48,850 --> 01:35:50,150
本杰明
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Benjamin.{\r}

1207
01:35:51,150 --> 01:35:54,350
- 还记得我吗？ - 当然了 巴顿先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Do you remember me? - Well, sure I do, Mr. Button.{\r}

1208
01:35:55,050 --> 01:35:58,650
- 你这是怎么了？ - 该死的脚 感染了 那个…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- What happened to you? - Darn foot. Got infected, so...{\r}

1209
01:36:00,350 --> 01:36:01,550
欢迎回家 朋友
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Welcome home, my friend.{\r}

1210
01:36:04,250 --> 01:36:07,350
你还是喜欢把威士忌 和别的酒混起来喝啊
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I see you're still drinking your Sazerac with whiskey.{\r}

1211
01:36:07,450 --> 01:36:08,650
呵 习惯这东西
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Creature of habit.{\r}

1212
01:36:08,750 --> 01:36:10,850
你还常去波旁大道那边的工厂吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You still visiting the house on Bourbon Street?{\r}

1213
01:36:10,950 --> 01:36:12,750
很久没去了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Not for a long time.{\r}

1214
01:36:14,350 --> 01:36:16,450
说来有趣
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Interesting times, though.{\r}

1215
01:36:16,550 --> 01:36:20,950
我们一开始每天做四万个纽扣 到后来一天50万
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We went from making 40,000 to nearly half a million buttons a day.{\r}

1216
01:36:21,050 --> 01:36:23,050
厂里的工人多了十倍
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We employed 10 times the number of people.{\r}

1217
01:36:23,150 --> 01:36:25,650
我们没日没夜地工作
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We were operating around the clock.{\r}

1218
01:36:30,250 --> 01:36:31,550
说来惭愧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Damn shame.{\r}

1219
01:36:32,750 --> 01:36:35,650
战争让纽扣生意更红火了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}The war has been kind to the button industry.{\r}

1220
01:36:38,450 --> 01:36:39,750
知道嘛
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You know,{\r}

1221
01:36:42,050 --> 01:36:45,350
我病了 不知道还能活多久
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm sick. I don't know how much longer I have.{\r}

1222
01:36:45,450 --> 01:36:48,250
- 您也别太难过了 巴顿先生 - 别这么说…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- I'm sorry to hear that, Mr. Button. - No...{\r}

1223
01:36:49,650 --> 01:36:52,750
我没什么朋友 一直都是独来独往
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I don't have any people. I keep to myself.{\r}

1224
01:36:55,250 --> 01:36:58,250
但愿你不要介意 不过 如果有可能
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I hope you don't mind, but, whenever possible,{\r}

1225
01:36:58,350 --> 01:37:00,350
我希望你可以多陪陪我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'd enjoy your company.{\r}

1226
01:37:00,450 --> 01:37:02,950
如果力所能及 我当然会的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'll certainly do what I can.{\r}

1227
01:37:06,250 --> 01:37:09,150
本杰明 你懂纽扣生意吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Benjamin, do you know anything about buttons?{\r}

1228
01:37:12,750 --> 01:37:17,450
到现在 巴顿纽扣厂已经 在家族中传承了124年了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Now, Button's Buttons has been in our family for 124 years.{\r}

1229
01:37:18,050 --> 01:37:22,650
我的祖父是个裁缝 只在里士满开了间小裁缝铺
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}My grandfather was a tailor, and he had a small shop in Richmond.{\r}

1230
01:37:22,750 --> 01:37:25,150
内战过后 他搬到了新奥尔良
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}After the Civil War, he moved to New Orleans,{\r}

1231
01:37:25,250 --> 01:37:30,350
在那儿 我父亲奋发图强 开始经营自己的纽扣生意
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}where my father had the wisdom to make our own buttons.{\r}

1232
01:37:30,450 --> 01:37:35,250
于是 在他的大力改革下 小裁缝铺成长到了今天这样的规模
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}So, with his help, the tailor shop grew to this.{\r}

1233
01:37:36,050 --> 01:37:38,650
如今 我却连衣服都不会自己缝了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And today, I can't sew a stitch.{\r}

1234
01:37:42,850 --> 01:37:45,150
这故事真的很有意思
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}That's very, very interesting.{\r}

1235
01:37:48,650 --> 01:37:51,250
很显然 您自己干得也不错嘛
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You sure have done well for yourself.{\r}

1236
01:37:52,150 --> 01:37:56,250
那我能帮上什么忙呢 巴顿先生？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}So, what can I do for you, Mr. Button?{\r}

1237
01:37:58,750 --> 01:38:01,750
本杰明 你是我儿子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Benjamin? You're my son.{\r}

1238
01:38:09,350 --> 01:38:11,950
抱歉 我以前从没提起过
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm so sorry I never told you before.{\r}

1239
01:38:14,150 --> 01:38:17,550
你是大战结束那晚出生的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You were born the night the Great War ended.{\r}

1240
01:38:19,450 --> 01:38:23,150
你母亲难产而死
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Your mother died giving birth to you.{\r}

1241
01:38:24,650 --> 01:38:26,850
我以为你是怪物
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I thought you were a monster.{\r}

1242
01:38:30,350 --> 01:38:33,650
我向你母亲保证过 保证你会平平安安
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I promised your mother I'd make sure you were safe.{\r}

1243
01:38:40,050 --> 01:38:42,550
对不起 我不该抛弃你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I should never have abandoned you.{\r}

1244
01:38:46,650 --> 01:38:48,050
我母亲？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}My mother?{\r}

1245
01:38:49,350 --> 01:38:52,350
庞恰特雷恩湖边的避暑别墅
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}At the summer house on Lake Pontchartrain.{\r}

1246
01:38:52,450 --> 01:38:55,850
我小时候 总喜欢比大家早起
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}When I was a boy, I'd love to wake up before anyone else,{\r}

1247
01:38:55,950 --> 01:38:58,950
然后跑到湖边 迎接新一天的开始
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}run down to that lake and watch the day begin.{\r}

1248
01:39:00,650 --> 01:39:03,250
那时候 我觉得自己 好像是这世上唯一一个活人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It was as if I was the only one alive.{\r}

1249
01:39:05,050 --> 01:39:07,750
第一眼看到她 我就爱上她了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I fell in love the first time I saw her.{\r}

1250
01:39:08,350 --> 01:39:10,950
你母亲叫卡洛琳・墨菲
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Your mother's name was Caroline Murphy.{\r}

1251
01:39:11,650 --> 01:39:14,450
她在你爷爷的厨房里干活
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She worked in your grandfather's kitchen.{\r}

1252
01:39:17,750 --> 01:39:19,450
她是都柏林人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She's from Dublin.{\r}

1253
01:39:20,150 --> 01:39:24,550
1903年 她和她的兄弟姐妹 就到美国来谋生了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}In 1903, Caroline and all her brothers and sisters came to live here,{\r}

1254
01:39:24,650 --> 01:39:26,150
就住在新奥尔良
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}in New Orleans.{\r}

1255
01:39:28,250 --> 01:39:31,150
我常常找借口下厨房
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'd find excuses to go down to that kitchen{\r}

1256
01:39:31,950 --> 01:39:34,050
就为了看她一眼
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}just so I could look at her.{\r}

1257
01:39:40,450 --> 01:39:44,150
1918年4月25号 那天 是我一生中最快乐的时光
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}April 25th, 1918. Happiest day of my life.{\r}

1258
01:39:44,950 --> 01:39:47,150
那天 我迎娶了你母亲
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}The day I married your mother.{\r}

1259
01:39:48,950 --> 01:39:51,050
你为什么不早点告诉我？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Why didn't you just tell me?{\r}

1260
01:39:51,950 --> 01:39:54,750
我准备把遗产都留给你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I plan on leaving everything I have to you.{\r}

1261
01:39:56,350 --> 01:39:58,750
- 我该走了 - 去哪？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- I have to go. - Where?{\r}

1262
01:39:59,850 --> 01:40:01,150
回家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Home.{\r}

1263
01:40:01,850 --> 01:40:03,250
他怎么想的 嗯？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And what does he think, anyway?{\r}

1264
01:40:03,350 --> 01:40:04,650
他以为自己这么冒出来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He thinks he can just show up{\r}

1265
01:40:04,750 --> 01:40:06,550
然后就没事了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}and everything's supposed to be fine and dandy.{\r}

1266
01:40:06,650 --> 01:40:09,250
然后大家就能做朋友了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Everybody's just supposed to be friends.{\r}

1267
01:40:09,350 --> 01:40:12,250
要我说 这事我跟他没完
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, he got another thing coming, that's for sure.{\r}

1268
01:40:12,350 --> 01:40:15,750
老天有眼 我跟他没完！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}God be my witness, he got another thing coming.{\r}

1269
01:40:15,850 --> 01:40:18,950
他丢掉你那晚 只留了18块钱
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He left us $18 that night you was found.{\r}

1270
01:40:19,050 --> 01:40:20,850
18张皱巴巴的票子！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Eighteen ratty dollars{\r}

1271
01:40:20,950 --> 01:40:22,650
- 还有一块脏兮兮的尿布 - 晚安了 妈
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- and a filthy diaper. - Good night, Mama.{\r}

1272
01:40:24,050 --> 01:40:25,250
晚安 宝贝儿
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Good night, baby.{\r}

1273
01:40:38,550 --> 01:40:42,850
我有没有跟你说过 我被闪电击中过七次？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Did I ever tell you I was struck by lightning seven times?{\r}

1274
01:40:44,650 --> 01:40:46,750
有一次 我就那么好好得遛着狗
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Once, I was walking my dog down the road.{\r}

1275
01:40:51,750 --> 01:40:55,550
现在我瞎了一只眼 几乎听不见
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm blind in the one eye, can't hardly hear,{\r}

1276
01:40:56,850 --> 01:41:01,450
还无缘无故抽搐发抖 老是忘东西
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}get twitches and shakes out of nowhere, always losing my line of thought.{\r}

1277
01:41:03,050 --> 01:41:04,650
但你知道嘛？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But you know what?{\r}

1278
01:41:05,450 --> 01:41:08,350
老天爷总是不断地提醒我 让我知道自己还活着 有多幸运
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}God keeps reminding me I'm lucky to be alive.{\r}

1279
01:41:14,150 --> 01:41:15,650
暴风雨快来了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Storm's coming.{\r}

1280
01:41:43,650 --> 01:41:45,850
可以为您效劳吗？ 楼上 第一间卧室
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}May I help you, sir? Up the stairs, first bedroom.{\r}

1281
01:41:45,950 --> 01:41:47,050
谢谢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Thank you.{\r}

1282
01:42:02,850 --> 01:42:04,150
醒醒
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Wake up.{\r}

1283
01:42:06,650 --> 01:42:08,550
我来帮你穿上衣服
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Let's get you dressed.{\r}

1284
01:42:35,950 --> 01:42:37,550
对 就这样
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Now that's something.{\r}

1285
01:42:40,950 --> 01:42:42,250
谢谢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Thank you.{\r}

1286
01:43:42,350 --> 01:43:46,350
不顺心的时候 你可以像疯狗那样发狂
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You can be mad as a mad dog at the way things went.{\r}

1287
01:43:46,450 --> 01:43:48,850
你可以破口大骂 诅咒命运
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You can swear and curse the Fates.{\r}

1288
01:43:50,450 --> 01:43:52,650
但到头来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But when it comes to the end,{\r}

1289
01:43:53,950 --> 01:43:55,650
还是得放手
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}you have to let go.{\r}

1290
01:44:17,650 --> 01:44:20,250
这葬礼很体面
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, it sure is a beautiful service.{\r}

1291
01:44:22,150 --> 01:44:24,950
他会葬在你母亲旁边
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He'll be buried right next to your mother.{\r}

1292
01:44:26,350 --> 01:44:28,050
您就是我母亲
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You're my mother.{\r}

1293
01:44:31,850 --> 01:44:33,050
我的孩子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}My baby.{\r}

1294
01:44:37,650 --> 01:44:39,850
我以前还从没来过纽约
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Now, I'd never seen New York.{\r}

1295
01:46:08,050 --> 01:46:11,350
- 打扰下 我是黛西的朋友 - 这边
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Excuse me, I'm a friend of Daisy's. - Right this way.{\r}

1296
01:46:12,450 --> 01:46:17,750
- 黛西有人找 黛西！ - 来了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Daisy has company. Daisy! Daisy! - Yes!{\r}

1297
01:46:18,150 --> 01:46:21,450
- 我们要放衣服 - 是谁找我呀？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- We need the wardrobe. - Is somebody looking for me?{\r}

1298
01:46:24,050 --> 01:46:26,250
- 本杰明 - 嗨
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Benjamin. - Hi.{\r}

1299
01:46:27,550 --> 01:46:31,350
- 你来这做什么？ - 我觉得应该来看看你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- What are you doing here? - Thought I'd come visit.{\r}

1300
01:46:31,450 --> 01:46:34,850
要是可以 约你出去转转
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Spend some time with you, if I could.{\r}

1301
01:46:35,050 --> 01:46:40,850
真希望你事先给我个电话 这样我都没法准备
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, well, I wish you would've called. You took me by surprise.{\r}

1302
01:46:42,250 --> 01:46:46,350
- 要是不喜欢就扔了吧 - 哪里 谢了 花很好看
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- You can just throw them out. - No. Thank you, they're lovely.{\r}

1303
01:46:47,050 --> 01:46:51,850
我从头到尾都在看你 你真是…太迷人了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I couldn't take my eyes off of you. I thought you were mesmerizing.{\r}

1304
01:46:53,850 --> 01:46:56,650
谢谢 谢谢你这么说
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Thank you. That's very kind of you to say.{\r}

1305
01:47:01,950 --> 01:47:04,050
我得去换身衣服了 我们几个要去聚会下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I better get changed. A group of us are going to a party.{\r}

1306
01:47:04,150 --> 01:47:07,350
- 你来吗？ - 听人说有家餐馆不错
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Would you want to come? - Someone told me about a restaurant{\r}

1307
01:47:07,550 --> 01:47:08,750
你应该也会喜欢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I thought you might enjoy.{\r}

1308
01:47:08,850 --> 01:47:11,350
我定了位 算是以防万一
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I made a reservation, just in case.{\r}

1309
01:47:11,450 --> 01:47:14,450
不过我们跳完舞之后都会聚聚…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Just, all the dancers go out after the show. You're...{\r}

1310
01:47:14,550 --> 01:47:18,350
你来我们会很欢迎的 我去换衣服 好吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You're welcome to come with us. I'll get changed. All right?{\r}

1311
01:47:24,850 --> 01:47:26,950
她还给俄罗斯芭蕾舞团排过舞
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She choreographs for the Ballets Russes.{\r}

1312
01:47:27,050 --> 01:47:28,350
太神了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She's divine.{\r}

1313
01:47:28,950 --> 01:47:30,850
你真美
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You were breathtaking.{\r}

1314
01:47:36,550 --> 01:47:37,750
小甜心
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Sweetie.{\r}

1315
01:47:38,950 --> 01:47:41,850
这是大卫 他也是舞团的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}This is David. He dances with the company.{\r}

1316
01:47:42,850 --> 01:47:44,850
- 这是本杰明 - 谁？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- This is Benjamin. - Who?{\r}

1317
01:47:44,950 --> 01:47:48,150
- 我跟你说起过他的 - 哦 是你啊 近来可好啊
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- I told you about him. - Oh, yeah. How you doing?{\r}

1318
01:47:48,250 --> 01:47:51,750
- 我去给你拿杯喝的 - 嗯 谢了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- I'll go get you a drink. - All right. Thanks.{\r}

1319
01:47:59,450 --> 01:48:02,650
这么说 你是她奶奶的朋友？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}So, you were a friend of her grandmother's?{\r}

1320
01:48:02,750 --> 01:48:04,650
还是就那一类的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Or something like that?{\r}

1321
01:48:05,750 --> 01:48:07,550
差不多吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Something like that.{\r}

1322
01:48:07,850 --> 01:48:09,450
嘿 失陪
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Hey, excuse me.{\r}

1323
01:48:31,750 --> 01:48:33,050
来吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Come on.{\r}

1324
01:48:54,350 --> 01:48:55,450
嘿！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Hey!{\r}

1325
01:48:56,450 --> 01:48:58,950
我真不知道你会来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Now, I had no idea you were coming.{\r}

1326
01:48:59,950 --> 01:49:01,450
天啊 本杰明
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Lord, Benjamin.{\r}

1327
01:49:04,050 --> 01:49:07,950
你想要我怎样呢？ 难道要我丢下这一切 跟你走吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What did you expect? What, you want me to drop everything?{\r}

1328
01:49:08,050 --> 01:49:10,050
这可是我的人生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Now, this is my life.{\r}

1329
01:49:10,150 --> 01:49:12,550
宝贝儿 去市中心不？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Babe! You going downtown?{\r}

1330
01:49:17,550 --> 01:49:20,650
来吧 你也会玩得很开心的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Come on. You'll have a good time.{\r}

1331
01:49:21,550 --> 01:49:22,950
那儿有很多音乐家和有趣的人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There's lots of musicians, interesting people.{\r}

1332
01:49:23,150 --> 01:49:26,050
真的不用了 都是我不好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You don't have to do that. This is my fault.{\r}

1333
01:49:27,150 --> 01:49:28,550
我是该先打个电话
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I should've called.{\r}

1334
01:49:28,650 --> 01:49:31,450
我本以为我突然过来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I thought I'd come here{\r}

1335
01:49:31,550 --> 01:49:34,250
会给你一个大惊喜
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}and sweep you off your feet or something.{\r}

1336
01:49:35,750 --> 01:49:40,250
- 黛西 快来吧 出发了！ - 马上到
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Daisy! Come on! Let's go. - Be right there.{\r}

1337
01:49:42,050 --> 01:49:43,450
他看来还不错
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Seems nice.{\r}

1338
01:49:44,750 --> 01:49:46,350
你爱他吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Do you love him?{\r}

1339
01:49:49,550 --> 01:49:50,850
应该吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I think so.{\r}

1340
01:49:53,050 --> 01:49:54,650
真替你高兴
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm happy for you.{\r}

1341
01:49:56,650 --> 01:49:58,750
那老家见吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Maybe I'll see you at home.{\r}

1342
01:50:01,350 --> 01:50:02,450
好吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Okay.{\r}

1343
01:50:04,550 --> 01:50:06,250
我很喜欢你的演出！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I enjoyed the show!{\r}

1344
01:50:13,850 --> 01:50:18,350
他来 是想告诉我 他父亲死了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He came to tell me his father had died.{\r}

1345
01:50:19,850 --> 01:50:26,050
- 你也猜不到啊 - 我那时才23岁 我…只是不在乎这些
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- You couldn't have known. - I was 23. I... I just didn't care.{\r}

1346
01:50:28,650 --> 01:50:30,050
那你后来呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What did you do next?{\r}

1347
01:50:30,150 --> 01:50:37,050
有些照片 我记得 就放在包的前袋里
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Some photographs, I think, in the front of my bag.{\r}

1348
01:50:39,150 --> 01:50:43,250
我那会还挺了不得
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I was as good a dancer as I was ever gonna be.{\r}

1349
01:50:45,150 --> 01:50:47,050
有那么五年 我…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}For five years, I...{\r}

1350
01:50:49,850 --> 01:50:51,650
在世界各地表演
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I danced everywhere.{\r}

1351
01:50:53,050 --> 01:50:56,550
伦敦 维也纳 布拉格
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}London, Vienna, Prague.{\r}

1352
01:50:57,150 --> 01:50:59,050
我从没见过这些照片
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I've never seen these.{\r}

1353
01:51:02,450 --> 01:51:03,450
妈
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Mom.{\r}

1354
01:51:04,750 --> 01:51:07,450
你从来没提你跳舞的事
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You never talked about your dancing.{\r}

1355
01:51:07,550 --> 01:51:09,550
我还是头一个
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, I was the only American{\r}

1356
01:51:09,650 --> 01:51:14,650
受邀 和大剧院舞团共舞的美国人 （Bolshoi：俄国著名芭蕾舞团）
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}to be invited to dance with the Bolshoi, sugar.{\r}

1357
01:51:16,450 --> 01:51:18,450
那真是太棒了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It was glorious.{\r}

1358
01:51:22,950 --> 01:51:26,650
但我从没忘记本杰明
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But Benjamin was never far from my thoughts.{\r}

1359
01:51:29,850 --> 01:51:33,350
有时候 我会不自觉地说…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And I'd find myself saying...{\r}

1360
01:51:33,550 --> 01:51:35,250
晚安 本杰明
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Good night, Benjamin.{\r}

1361
01:51:37,350 --> 01:51:40,950
- “晚安 黛西” - 他也这么说？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- "Good night, Daisy." - He said that?{\r}

1362
01:51:43,150 --> 01:51:44,250
“生活并没有那么复杂
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"Life wasn't all that complicated.{\r}

1363
01:51:45,150 --> 01:51:47,950
要是你喜欢 大可以说我是在探索生命”
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"If you want, you might say I was looking for something."{\r}

1364
01:51:57,350 --> 01:52:00,350
本杰明 拉・图尔诺夫人刚刚过世了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Benjamin? Mrs. La Tourneau just passed.{\r}

1365
01:52:06,750 --> 01:52:10,450
- 本杰明・巴顿先生的信 - 我就是
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Letter for Mr. Benjamin Button? - That'd be me.{\r}

1366
01:52:13,350 --> 01:52:14,650
谢谢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Thank you.{\r}

1367
01:52:41,050 --> 01:52:42,950
我找黛西・富勒小姐
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Miss Daisy Fuller.{\r}

1368
01:52:43,050 --> 01:52:45,850
- 稍等 请先坐一会 - 好的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Just a minute. Please have a seat. - Sure.{\r}

1369
01:52:53,250 --> 01:52:57,650
有时候 我们的人生轨道 会与别人的交错 只是不自知罢了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Sometimes we're on a collision course and we just don't know it.{\r}

1370
01:52:58,250 --> 01:53:02,750
无论是意外 还是天意 我们都无力改变
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Whether it's by accident or by design, there's not a thing we can do about it.{\r}

1371
01:53:05,550 --> 01:53:08,650
巴黎 一名女子正要出门购物
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}A woman in Paris was on her way to go shopping.{\r}

1372
01:53:09,950 --> 01:53:13,750
却发现忘带外套 于是回家去取
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But she had forgotten her coat, went back to get it.{\r}

1373
01:53:13,850 --> 01:53:16,050
她拿起外套 电话铃响
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}When she had gotten her coat, the phone had rung.{\r}

1374
01:53:16,150 --> 01:53:19,150
她接起电话 聊了一会
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}So she had stopped to answer it and talked for a couple of minutes.{\r}

1375
01:53:20,650 --> 01:53:22,450
与此同时
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}While the woman was on the phone,{\r}

1376
01:53:22,550 --> 01:53:26,750
黛西正为一场巴黎歌剧院的演出彩排
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Daisy was rehearsing for a performance at the Paris Opera House.{\r}

1377
01:53:26,850 --> 01:53:29,550
不久 女子聊完 挂了电话
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And while she was rehearsing, the woman, off the phone now,{\r}

1378
01:53:29,650 --> 01:53:31,950
下楼去招出租车
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}had gone outside to get a taxi.{\r}

1379
01:53:36,550 --> 01:53:38,850
另一边 出租车司机 刚刚送完一位客人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Now, a taxi driver had dropped off a fare earlier,{\r}

1380
01:53:38,950 --> 01:53:41,650
便停了车 去买咖啡
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}and had stopped to get a cup of coffee.{\r}

1381
01:53:42,550 --> 01:53:45,250
而黛西还在继续排练
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And all the while, Daisy was rehearsing.{\r}

1382
01:53:48,850 --> 01:53:51,350
那位送完了客人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And this cab driver, who dropped off the earlier fare{\r}

1383
01:53:51,450 --> 01:53:53,350
便去买咖啡的司机
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}and had stopped to get the cup of coffee,{\r}

1384
01:53:53,450 --> 01:53:55,150
正巧接了要去购物的那位女子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}he picked up the lady who was going shopping{\r}

1385
01:53:55,250 --> 01:53:57,950
而那位女子 因为一番延误 刚错过了之前的车
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}and had missed getting the earlier cab.{\r}

1386
01:53:58,950 --> 01:54:01,350
车子中途停了一下 因为有人横穿马路
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}The taxi had to stop for a man crossing the street,{\r}

1387
01:54:01,450 --> 01:54:04,250
这位男子那天比平时晚起了五分钟
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}who had left for work five minutes later than he normally did{\r}

1388
01:54:04,350 --> 01:54:06,850
因为他忘了定闹钟
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}because he forgot to set his alarm.{\r}

1389
01:54:07,650 --> 01:54:10,950
那个没定闹钟 早上迟到的人 横穿马路的时候
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}While that man, late for work, was crossing the street,{\r}

1390
01:54:11,050 --> 01:54:14,450
黛西已经排练结束 开始冲澡
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Daisy had finished rehearsing and was taking a shower.{\r}

1391
01:54:14,950 --> 01:54:16,250
她在洗澡的时候
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And while Daisy was showering,{\r}

1392
01:54:16,350 --> 01:54:20,050
出租车停在一家糖果店门口 等女客人去取包裹
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}the taxi was waiting outside a boutique for the woman to pick up a package{\r}

1393
01:54:20,150 --> 01:54:21,250
可包裹还没备好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}which hadn't been wrapped yet,{\r}

1394
01:54:21,350 --> 01:54:23,150
因为打包的女孩
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}because the girl who was supposed to wrap it{\r}

1395
01:54:23,250 --> 01:54:26,850
